# Trivy ignore file — consumed by the CI "Scan app image (Trivy)" gate
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml, mounted into the Trivy container via --ignorefile).
# One CVE ID per line. Every entry MUST carry a justification and a re-review
# trigger. Do NOT add blanket ignores here to silence the gate — fix (bump the
# dep) unless there is a documented reason.
#
# This list is kept in LOCK-STEP with the pip-audit `--ignore-vuln` list in the
# same workflow: every CVE below is already an accepted risk there (Trivy keys
# off CVE/GHSA IDs, pip-audit off the equivalent PYSEC IDs). If you clear an
# entry in one gate, clear it in the other.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cryptography (pinned ==46.0.7). Bundled OpenSSL advisory. The only fix is a
# 46 -> 48.x MAJOR jump; PYSEC-2026-35/36 are already patched via 46.0.7.
# pip-audit equivalent: GHSA-537c-gmf6-5ccf (ci.yml). Drop when we do the
# framework-upgrade pass that moves cryptography to 48.x.
GHSA-537c-gmf6-5ccf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# pyasn1 (resolves to 0.4.8). DoS via unbounded recursion. Fix is 0.6.3, but
# python-jose==3.4.0 caps pyasn1<0.5.0, so it cannot be bumped without a
# python-jose upgrade. pip-audit equivalent: PYSEC-2026-2263. Drop when
# python-jose is upgraded to a release that allows pyasn1>=0.6.3.
CVE-2026-30922

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# starlette (pinned transitively by fastapi==0.104.1 -> starlette==0.27.0).
# All three below require a fastapi 0.109+ / starlette 0.40+ (some 1.x) MAJOR
# upgrade that also drags pydantic. Accepted for now, mitigated by the
# Cloudflare Tunnel + per-client rate limiter (app/core/limiter.py). pip-audit
# equivalents: PYSEC-2024-38 / PYSEC-2026-161 / PYSEC-2026-248 / PYSEC-2026-249.
# Drop all three when fastapi is bumped to a starlette>=1.3.1 release.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Multipart/form-data DoS. Reachable (the app accepts file uploads), but bounded
# by the tunnel + rate limiter; real fix is the fastapi upgrade above.
CVE-2024-47874

# SSRF / NTLM credential theft via UNC paths in StaticFiles. UNC paths are a
# Windows-only construct; this backend runs on Debian containers, so the code
# path is not reachable. Re-review if the app is ever run on Windows.
CVE-2026-48818

# request.form() size limits silently ignored for application/x-www-form-
# urlencoded bodies -> DoS. Low severity; already mitigated by the per-client
# rate limiter (app/core/limiter.py). Drop when fastapi is bumped to a release
# that pins starlette>=1.3.1.
CVE-2026-54283
